38
00:01:49,360 --> 00:01:51,280
♪Let's travel together
to the ends of the earth♪

39
00:01:52,660 --> 00:01:56,710
[Practice Daughter]

40
00:01:56,710 --> 00:02:00,660
[Adapted from An Yimo's original novel,
The Charming Thief Princess]

41
00:02:01,610 --> 00:02:04,100
[Episode 13]

42
00:02:13,020 --> 00:02:14,100
They must have

43
00:02:15,980 --> 00:02:17,700
switched their bodies back.

44
00:02:45,340 --> 00:02:46,180
How come?

45
00:02:46,340 --> 00:02:47,100
Don't worry.

46
00:02:47,100 --> 00:02:48,620
I think a broken one also works.

47
00:02:48,620 --> 00:02:49,780
A broken one also works?

48
00:02:49,860 --> 00:02:51,180
Let's give it a try.

49
00:03:04,020 --> 00:03:05,620
Now we won't be able to switch back.

50
00:03:07,020 --> 00:03:08,740
Do you think

51
00:03:09,020 --> 00:03:11,020
it was because we were both holding it?

52
00:03:12,100 --> 00:03:13,460
It was all your fault.

53
00:03:13,780 --> 00:03:14,620
My fault?

54
00:03:14,780 --> 00:03:16,220
If you hadn't tried
to steal it from the Museum,

55
00:03:16,220 --> 00:03:17,220
how could this happen?

56
00:03:17,460 --> 00:03:18,980
It was all that idiot's fault.

57
00:03:19,340 --> 00:03:22,100
She called this pearl
the one no thief could steal,

58
00:03:22,100 --> 00:03:23,300
which made my fathers

59
00:03:23,300 --> 00:03:24,620
so excited.

60
00:03:24,620 --> 00:03:27,100
They insisted
on proving their stealing skills.

61
00:03:27,100 --> 00:03:28,140
What to do now?

62
00:03:28,460 --> 00:03:29,540
I can't even leave the palace.

63
00:03:29,540 --> 00:03:30,700
How would I know what to do?

64
00:03:30,980 --> 00:03:32,620
If I have to be your maid forever,

65
00:03:32,620 --> 00:03:34,140
how miserable my life will be?

66
00:03:34,540 --> 00:03:35,820
I'm the miserable one.

67
00:03:36,020 --> 00:03:37,100
Being the daughter
of the Grand Chancellor,

68
00:03:37,100 --> 00:03:38,180
I have so many rules to follow.

69
00:03:38,180 --> 00:03:39,060
I have to read and study.

70
00:03:39,060 --> 00:03:40,060
I can't even eat as much food as I want.

71
00:03:40,340 --> 00:03:41,500
Keep your voice down.

72
00:03:42,100 --> 00:03:43,100
I'll still have to serve you

73
00:03:43,100 --> 00:03:44,380
when I grow old.

74
00:03:44,500 --> 00:03:46,260
I don't want you to serve me.

75
00:04:05,220 --> 00:04:05,860
Oh no.

76
00:04:16,820 --> 00:04:17,900
Douzi is in danger.

77
00:04:20,820 --> 00:04:22,540
Disasters hit the Yellow River basin
every year.

78
00:04:23,020 --> 00:04:24,300
We've tried to control it all the time.

79
00:04:24,620 --> 00:04:25,180
The rainy season came.

80
00:04:25,180 --> 00:04:26,100
But no one took precautions...

81
00:04:26,100 --> 00:04:26,460
Miss Mei.

82
00:04:26,460 --> 00:04:27,180
What do we
keep those local officers for?

83
00:04:27,180 --> 00:04:28,420
I want to talk

84
00:04:28,420 --> 00:04:29,420
to His Highness.

85
00:04:29,900 --> 00:04:30,500
Useless.

86
00:04:30,540 --> 00:04:31,380
Your Highness, please don't be mad.

87
00:04:31,460 --> 00:04:33,020
I'll work on it now.

88
00:04:35,060 --> 00:04:35,700
It's fine.

89
00:04:35,820 --> 00:04:37,020
Don't worry, Miss Mei.

90
00:04:37,340 --> 00:04:39,580
There's a lot going on these days.

91
00:04:39,580 --> 00:04:41,180
His Highness has not slept all night.

92
00:04:44,060 --> 00:04:44,660
Nanbei.

93
00:04:45,700 --> 00:04:46,620
Go get the Vice Minister
of the Ministry of Revenue.

94
00:04:47,340 --> 00:04:47,980
Yes.

95
00:04:51,700 --> 00:04:52,860
Douzi...?

96
00:04:58,500 --> 00:04:59,220
Mei Yushan.

97
00:05:00,580 --> 00:05:02,780
It's me, Little Master.

98
00:05:04,940 --> 00:05:06,140
What are you here for?

99
00:05:08,300 --> 00:05:10,380
It's nothing urgent.

100
00:05:11,180 --> 00:05:12,980
Your Highness, Miss Mei is here to...

101
00:05:14,340 --> 00:05:15,580
I have a business to discuss.

102
00:05:17,380 --> 00:05:18,500
Please leave if you're not involved.

103
00:05:28,180 --> 00:05:28,900
Miss Mei,

104
00:05:29,380 --> 00:05:31,140
maybe you should go back.

105
00:05:32,660 --> 00:05:33,340
You may leave.

106
00:05:56,860 --> 00:05:58,020
There was a full moon last night.

107
00:05:58,740 --> 00:06:00,500
Why hasn't she left the palace yet?

108
00:06:05,380 --> 00:06:07,660
This article should be recited in pairs

109
00:06:07,660 --> 00:06:08,860
with different roles.

110
00:06:09,300 --> 00:06:10,820
Please find your own partners.

111
00:06:11,100 --> 00:06:11,860
Begin.

112
00:06:11,980 --> 00:06:12,700
This is...

113
00:06:12,700 --> 00:06:13,700
Let's do it together.

114
00:06:15,100 --> 00:06:15,900
How to read this?

115
00:06:15,900 --> 00:06:16,500
Mei...

116
00:06:17,460 --> 00:06:19,100
She's waiting for the Crown Prince.

117
00:06:19,100 --> 00:06:19,940
Leave her alone.

118
00:06:19,940 --> 00:06:20,820
Such a fool.

119
00:06:21,180 --> 00:06:21,860
Come here.

120
00:06:22,220 --> 00:06:23,100
Right.

121
00:06:23,460 --> 00:06:24,820
Let's split up into groups.

122
00:06:25,020 --> 00:06:25,660
Let's go.

123
00:06:25,780 --> 00:06:26,580
Come on, let's go.

124
00:06:27,100 --> 00:06:27,820
How do we do this?

125
00:06:27,820 --> 00:06:29,420
Why don't we play
a finger-guessing game to decide it?

126
00:06:29,420 --> 00:06:30,300
- Okay.
- Okay.

127
00:06:30,300 --> 00:06:30,980
Finger-guessing game.

128
00:06:31,260 --> 00:06:32,780
Come on, let's do this.

129
00:06:32,780 --> 00:06:34,740
One, two, three, go.

130
00:06:35,000 --> 00:06:40,310
♪Your gentle call awakens me
from my unfinished dreams♪

131
00:06:41,180 --> 00:06:42,700
Let's go.

132
00:06:42,700 --> 00:06:44,100
- Let's go.
- Oh, my back.

133
00:06:45,020 --> 00:06:45,740
Let's go.

134
00:06:46,100 --> 00:06:46,700
Come on.

135
00:06:47,970 --> 00:06:52,550
♪I am meant to accompany you
on this journey♪

136
00:06:52,940 --> 00:06:55,380
Miss Mei, you haven't finished
your assignment today, have you?

137
00:06:56,340 --> 00:06:58,380
Please finish it before you leave.

138
00:06:58,780 --> 00:07:00,100
Otherwise, I'll be blamed.

139
00:07:00,100 --> 00:07:05,370
♪You and I, each completing the other,
year after year♪

140
00:07:05,630 --> 00:07:08,470
♪Accompany me to explore the world♪

141
00:07:08,660 --> 00:07:11,830
♪We walk together on bustling streets♪

142
00:07:12,420 --> 00:07:17,670
♪My heart leans
towards your warm embrace♪

143
00:07:17,930 --> 00:07:21,940
♪We're both kites reclaimed
from the edge of the sky♪

144
00:07:21,940 --> 00:07:23,620
When Miss Mei went
to the Eastern Palace,

145
00:07:23,660 --> 00:07:24,660
you wouldn't see her.

146
00:07:24,980 --> 00:07:26,940
But now we come
to the Chongwen Academy every day.

147
00:07:27,260 --> 00:07:28,380
If you want to see Miss Mei,

148
00:07:28,380 --> 00:07:29,860
why don't we go inside?

149
00:07:34,340 --> 00:07:35,420
Are we really not going in?

150
00:07:40,300 --> 00:07:41,300
We're already here.

151
00:08:04,740 --> 00:08:05,460
Where are you going?

152
00:08:05,700 --> 00:08:07,500
I have always been a free spirit.

153
00:08:07,500 --> 00:08:08,900
But now I'm locked up
in a place like this,

154
00:08:08,900 --> 00:08:10,540
reciting those useless books.

155
00:08:10,620 --> 00:08:11,580
I've had enough.

156
00:08:11,580 --> 00:08:12,340
I'm not reciting anything anymore.

157
00:08:12,340 --> 00:08:13,180
Where are you going?

158
00:08:13,180 --> 00:08:14,020
Out of the palace.

159
00:08:14,020 --> 00:08:15,120
[Chongwen Academy]

160
00:08:15,420 --> 00:08:16,540
I've had enough.

161
00:08:16,540 --> 00:08:17,740
I need to leave the palace now.

162
00:08:17,740 --> 00:08:19,060
Where will you go then?

163
00:08:19,060 --> 00:08:19,660
I...

164
00:08:19,860 --> 00:08:21,340
I'll go to Xuanwu Street
to have a bowl of mutton soup.

165
00:08:21,340 --> 00:08:22,780
I'll take a day
doing nothing in the field.

166
00:08:22,780 --> 00:08:24,660
I'll ask my three fathers
to steal a wagon

167
00:08:24,660 --> 00:08:26,020
and get as far away from the palace

168
00:08:26,020 --> 00:08:27,020
as possible.

169
00:08:28,140 --> 00:08:29,620
Are you crazy?

170
00:08:29,620 --> 00:08:30,220
I...

171
00:08:30,300 --> 00:08:31,540
I'd rather be beheaded now

172
00:08:31,540 --> 00:08:32,420
than stay here.

173
00:08:34,900 --> 00:08:36,900
There are dozens of lives in my family.

174
00:08:36,900 --> 00:08:37,860
Have you ever thought about them?

175
00:08:37,860 --> 00:08:39,380
The Grand Chancellor's daughter
left the palace at night

176
00:08:39,740 --> 00:08:41,420
and eloped with three old men.

177
00:08:41,420 --> 00:08:42,620
People would even make up a story
based on it,

178
00:08:42,620 --> 00:08:43,700
which would be remembered
for a hundred years.

179
00:08:45,900 --> 00:08:48,620
You're so annoying.

180
00:08:53,740 --> 00:08:54,540
Besides,

181
00:08:54,540 --> 00:08:55,700
what am I going to do if you leave?

182
00:08:55,700 --> 00:08:57,540
Stay here and watch people laugh at you?

183
00:08:58,420 --> 00:09:00,300
Then let's leave together.

184
00:09:00,580 --> 00:09:02,140
Did I just say all that for nothing?

185
00:09:02,140 --> 00:09:03,300
Have you been listening?

186
00:09:03,940 --> 00:09:04,740
You won't leave?

187
00:09:04,980 --> 00:09:05,780
Well, I'm leaving.

188
00:09:07,020 --> 00:09:08,500
You can't leave.

189
00:09:08,580 --> 00:09:09,700
Let go of me.

190
00:09:09,700 --> 00:09:10,860
You can't leave.

191
00:09:10,860 --> 00:09:12,340
Let go.

192
00:09:12,660 --> 00:09:13,980
- You can't go.
- Let go.

193
00:09:15,940 --> 00:09:17,780
Let go of me.

194
00:10:17,860 --> 00:10:18,620
Are you okay?

195
00:10:18,620 --> 00:10:19,660
Are you still feeling bad?

196
00:10:24,420 --> 00:10:25,020
Your Highness.

197
00:10:25,740 --> 00:10:26,500
Are you okay?

198
00:10:27,500 --> 00:10:28,260
I'm fine.

199
00:10:30,620 --> 00:10:31,340
Little Diviner,

200
00:10:31,340 --> 00:10:32,500
thank you for saving my life.

201
00:10:33,580 --> 00:10:34,900
I couldn't see clearly underwater.

202
00:10:35,180 --> 00:10:36,380
I worried there might be water snakes,

203
00:10:36,380 --> 00:10:38,260
so I was trying
to pull you up desperately.

204
00:10:38,420 --> 00:10:39,500
I was so scared.

205
00:10:39,500 --> 00:10:40,580
I thought I was going to die.

206
00:10:40,580 --> 00:10:41,380
Fortunately, you are fine.

207
00:10:48,660 --> 00:10:49,620
- You've also got some water here.
- Really?

208
00:10:51,700 --> 00:10:52,380
Douzi.

209
00:10:54,060 --> 00:10:55,420
How could you be so careless?

210
00:10:56,180 --> 00:10:58,180
I was going to...

211
00:11:01,700 --> 00:11:03,220
I was trying to do some exercise.

212
00:11:03,220 --> 00:11:05,460
But maybe I've gained
some weight lately.

213
00:11:05,460 --> 00:11:07,300
So that railing couldn't save me.

214
00:11:08,660 --> 00:11:10,060
Why were you at the lake today?

215
00:11:11,740 --> 00:11:12,980
I was going to...

216
00:11:14,420 --> 00:11:15,060
Your Highness,

217
00:11:15,340 --> 00:11:16,020
are you okay?

218
00:11:16,020 --> 00:11:17,460
Why did you fall into the lake?

219
00:11:17,620 --> 00:11:18,300
I'm fine.

220
00:11:18,740 --> 00:11:19,420
Ask the Imperial Physicians

221
00:11:19,420 --> 00:11:20,540
to get some medicine for the cold.

222
00:11:24,060 --> 00:11:25,500
Thank you, Your Highness,
for saving my life.

223
00:11:25,660 --> 00:11:26,940
I am very grateful.

224
00:11:27,380 --> 00:11:27,980
You may rise.

225
00:11:28,420 --> 00:11:29,860
It was an urgent situation.
I had to save you.

226
00:11:42,700 --> 00:11:43,820
Just lie down.

227
00:11:43,820 --> 00:11:44,900
The Crown Prince
understands your gratitude.

228
00:12:03,700 --> 00:12:04,340
Mr. Bai.

229
00:12:04,820 --> 00:12:05,780
What's the matter?

230
00:12:06,060 --> 00:12:07,060
Go.

231
00:12:08,020 --> 00:12:10,540
Go look into Douzi's maid's background.

232
00:12:10,700 --> 00:12:11,300
Yes.

233
00:12:16,460 --> 00:12:17,580
How dare she!

234
00:12:18,260 --> 00:12:19,380
Your Majesty.

235
00:12:19,540 --> 00:12:20,980
Don't get so angry.

236
00:12:21,060 --> 00:12:22,220
I was the one

237
00:12:22,620 --> 00:12:24,340
who invited her to the palace.

238
00:12:25,180 --> 00:12:26,900
What a bad decision!

239
00:12:28,380 --> 00:12:29,340
How is Yao?

240
00:12:30,060 --> 00:12:32,300
Is he okay after falling into the water?

241
00:12:32,740 --> 00:12:34,900
His Highness hasn't left
the Eastern Palace ever since.

242
00:12:35,340 --> 00:12:37,420
He wouldn't allow physicians
to check on him, either.

243
00:12:38,940 --> 00:12:40,340
How improper!

244
00:12:59,340 --> 00:13:00,180
Stupid girl.

245
00:13:00,300 --> 00:13:01,620
Do you know how to comb hair or not?

246
00:13:01,820 --> 00:13:03,140
My Lady, your hair is too dry.

247
00:13:03,260 --> 00:13:04,580
I will go get some castor oil.

248
00:13:06,420 --> 00:13:07,020
Castor...

249
00:13:07,540 --> 00:13:08,860
Castor oil?

250
00:13:09,060 --> 00:13:10,700
Isn't castor oil used for cooking?

251
00:13:10,860 --> 00:13:11,580
Stupid girl,

252
00:13:11,580 --> 00:13:12,980
do you try to drown me with oil?

253
00:13:28,460 --> 00:13:30,060
Why did you summon me
so suddenly, Sir?

254
00:13:30,460 --> 00:13:32,580
I'm afraid it's not safe here.

255
00:13:32,820 --> 00:13:33,780
It is urgent.

256
00:13:34,060 --> 00:13:35,660
Do you still
have the Crown Prince's jade pendant?

257
00:13:36,380 --> 00:13:37,940
I have been keeping it on me,

258
00:13:37,940 --> 00:13:39,060
in case it might come in handy.

259
00:13:39,420 --> 00:13:40,020
Good.

260
00:13:40,420 --> 00:13:41,300
Try to sneak into Mei's room

261
00:13:41,300 --> 00:13:42,860
and put the plate there.

262
00:13:43,460 --> 00:13:44,540
Meanwhile, spread rumors

263
00:13:44,540 --> 00:13:45,660
saying she has a crush
on the Crown Prince.

264
00:13:46,020 --> 00:13:47,180
Why?

265
00:13:47,420 --> 00:13:48,580
Please enlighten me.

266
00:13:50,100 --> 00:13:51,580
After they got out of the water
this afternoon,

267
00:13:52,060 --> 00:13:54,140
Bai Ye looked at the princess
in a strange way.

268
00:13:54,900 --> 00:13:56,740
I suspect that he knows something now.

269
00:13:57,260 --> 00:13:58,060
Right now,

270
00:13:58,580 --> 00:13:59,660
we must get the princess

271
00:13:59,660 --> 00:14:00,780
out of the palace soon.

272
00:14:01,220 --> 00:14:03,100
A lot of maids had a crush
on the Crown Prince before,

273
00:14:03,300 --> 00:14:04,540
and they were all sent away.

274
00:14:05,940 --> 00:14:07,100
I really have no other choice

275
00:14:07,580 --> 00:14:08,900
but to send her away like this.

276
00:14:09,980 --> 00:14:11,140
Once we get her out,

277
00:14:11,740 --> 00:14:12,820
I'll ask someone to pick her up.

278
00:14:13,820 --> 00:14:14,900
But

279
00:14:15,300 --> 00:14:18,060
the Crown Prince
lost the pendant in the Museum.

280
00:14:18,660 --> 00:14:19,420
Don't forget

281
00:14:20,780 --> 00:14:22,220
the princess was also there that day.

282
00:14:22,700 --> 00:14:23,540
About that,

283
00:14:24,180 --> 00:14:25,260
she would have no explanation.

284
00:14:27,060 --> 00:14:27,900
I see.

285
00:14:27,900 --> 00:14:28,700
I'll get on it.

286
00:14:29,460 --> 00:14:30,060
By the way,

287
00:14:30,460 --> 00:14:31,420
this is important.

288
00:14:31,660 --> 00:14:33,380
The princess must not find out about it.

289
00:14:34,580 --> 00:14:35,180
She won't.

290
00:14:35,260 --> 00:14:36,980
She fell ill coming out of the water.

291
00:14:36,980 --> 00:14:38,260
I think she has a cold.

292
00:14:44,980 --> 00:14:46,100
Douzi.

293
00:14:55,540 --> 00:14:56,780
Why is it so hot?

294
00:15:00,580 --> 00:15:01,460
How do you feel?

295
00:15:01,740 --> 00:15:03,020
It hurts everywhere.

296
00:15:03,300 --> 00:15:04,980
I felt cold when I got out
of the water this afternoon.

297
00:15:05,460 --> 00:15:06,900
I feel even colder now.

298
00:15:07,100 --> 00:15:08,660
What's going on?

299
00:15:08,700 --> 00:15:10,540
Why isn't the medicine working?

300
00:15:11,300 --> 00:15:12,500
The pain is tolerable.

301
00:15:13,460 --> 00:15:15,500
A lot of people
saw us falling into the lake.

302
00:15:16,020 --> 00:15:18,140
If the Empress finds out,

303
00:15:18,500 --> 00:15:21,020
she'll blame us
for making the Crown Prince suffer.

304
00:15:22,180 --> 00:15:23,900
Is she going to punish us?

305
00:15:23,980 --> 00:15:24,900
It's okay if she punishes me,

306
00:15:24,900 --> 00:15:26,220
but she can't punish you.

307
00:15:27,340 --> 00:15:29,500
Even though you are
the Grand Chancellor's daughter,

308
00:15:29,660 --> 00:15:31,820
the empress will still blame you.

309
00:15:32,180 --> 00:15:33,340
Not to mention me.

310
00:15:34,420 --> 00:15:36,300
Then I'll beg Little Master

311
00:15:36,300 --> 00:15:37,300
to put in a good word for us.

312
00:15:37,900 --> 00:15:38,820
Right, I'll beg Little Master.

313
00:15:38,820 --> 00:15:39,940
Not now.

314
00:15:40,420 --> 00:15:41,540
The empress

315
00:15:42,340 --> 00:15:44,020
will visit His Highness for sure.

316
00:15:44,780 --> 00:15:45,740
Douzi?

317
00:15:46,740 --> 00:15:47,540
Douzi.

318
00:15:47,540 --> 00:15:50,410
[Eastern Palace]

319
00:15:53,900 --> 00:15:56,020
Open the gate, please.

320
00:15:57,220 --> 00:15:57,860
Thank you.

321
00:15:59,140 --> 00:16:00,220
- The Crown Prince has said before...
- Well...

322
00:16:00,540 --> 00:16:01,660
whenever she comes,

323
00:16:02,300 --> 00:16:03,140
she can go in.

324
00:16:05,540 --> 00:16:06,540
Little Master?

325
00:16:06,700 --> 00:16:08,100
Little Master, are you in?

326
00:16:08,500 --> 00:16:09,620
Little Master, are you in there?

327
00:16:09,620 --> 00:16:11,380
His Highness is taking a bath.
Please wait.

328
00:16:11,380 --> 00:16:12,380
Little Master.

329
00:16:12,820 --> 00:16:14,020
Douzi?

330
00:16:17,300 --> 00:16:18,380
The night of the full moon has passed.

331
00:16:18,780 --> 00:16:19,700
Why haven't you left yet?

332
00:16:20,060 --> 00:16:22,540
I'm afraid

333
00:16:22,700 --> 00:16:24,580
I'll be staying for a while.

334
00:16:25,460 --> 00:16:25,820
Why?

335
00:16:26,420 --> 00:16:28,940
The night of the full moon,

336
00:16:28,940 --> 00:16:30,620
the pearl somehow broke
when we tried to switch bodies.

337
00:16:31,940 --> 00:16:32,980
She really can't leave?

338
00:16:34,140 --> 00:16:35,260
That is good news.

339
00:16:35,500 --> 00:16:38,180
If I had put the Moon Spirit Pearl
in my pocket

340
00:16:38,180 --> 00:16:39,020
instead of taking it out,

341
00:16:39,020 --> 00:16:40,340
maybe it wouldn't have broken.

342
00:16:41,340 --> 00:16:42,940
What do I do now?

343
00:16:45,100 --> 00:16:46,180
So what are you

344
00:16:47,540 --> 00:16:48,420
going to do next?

345
00:16:49,260 --> 00:16:51,060
I don't know what to do.

346
00:16:52,460 --> 00:16:53,020
By the way,

347
00:16:53,020 --> 00:16:54,620
why did you show up

348
00:16:54,620 --> 00:16:55,620
as soon as I fell today?

349
00:16:57,100 --> 00:16:58,260
I was just passing by.

350
00:17:00,500 --> 00:17:02,540
Coming back to the Eastern Palace,

351
00:17:02,740 --> 00:17:04,780
you don't need to pass that lake.

352
00:17:06,020 --> 00:17:06,660
What now?

353
00:17:06,980 --> 00:17:07,980
Are you interrogating me?

354
00:17:08,260 --> 00:17:09,740
Who are you to decide
which way I take?

355
00:17:10,500 --> 00:17:11,180
Besides,

356
00:17:11,940 --> 00:17:13,380
why didn't you tell me sooner

357
00:17:13,540 --> 00:17:14,820
that you couldn't switch bodies?

358
00:17:16,020 --> 00:17:17,660
I was depressed for nothing these days.

359
00:17:17,740 --> 00:17:18,340
I...

360
00:17:18,660 --> 00:17:20,260
I wanted to tell you.

361
00:17:20,700 --> 00:17:22,620
I came looking for you.

362
00:17:22,620 --> 00:17:23,780
But you told me

363
00:17:23,780 --> 00:17:24,940
to leave

364
00:17:24,940 --> 00:17:26,180
because I was not involved.

365
00:17:28,580 --> 00:17:29,620
So you feel wronged.

366
00:17:29,980 --> 00:17:31,340
Of course, I feel wronged.

367
00:17:31,500 --> 00:17:33,180
I didn't know anyone here.

368
00:17:33,180 --> 00:17:35,260
Finally, I had a Little Master,

369
00:17:35,460 --> 00:17:37,260
but he gave me the cold shoulder.

370
00:17:41,260 --> 00:17:42,940
I remember someone said

371
00:17:47,220 --> 00:17:49,140
that ducklings had their own thoughts.

372
00:17:59,660 --> 00:18:02,260
What does this
have to do with ducklings?

373
00:18:03,580 --> 00:18:06,620
Well, that friend of yours...

374
00:18:07,300 --> 00:18:09,060
The little duckling.

375
00:18:09,300 --> 00:18:11,060
Did it go back to its pond

376
00:18:11,060 --> 00:18:13,140
or was it made into a roast duck?

377
00:18:20,100 --> 00:18:20,980
Yao?

378
00:18:22,300 --> 00:18:23,140
Yao.

379
00:18:24,700 --> 00:18:25,820
What to do? What to do?

380
00:18:25,820 --> 00:18:26,740
Little Master, what do we do?

381
00:18:26,740 --> 00:18:28,420
What to do? What to do?

382
00:18:29,140 --> 00:18:30,020
What are you afraid of?

383
00:18:30,300 --> 00:18:31,580
Just come out with me.

384
00:18:31,860 --> 00:18:32,820
My mother won't kill you.

385
00:18:32,820 --> 00:18:33,420
No.

386
00:18:33,420 --> 00:18:35,260
She... She must be here

387
00:18:35,300 --> 00:18:36,180
to look for trouble

388
00:18:36,180 --> 00:18:37,140
because I fell into the water.

389
00:18:37,140 --> 00:18:37,660
If she finds out

390
00:18:37,660 --> 00:18:38,900
that I'm here watching you shower,

391
00:18:38,900 --> 00:18:40,740
it will make her even more furious.

392
00:18:40,820 --> 00:18:42,260
When did you watch me shower?

393
00:18:42,260 --> 00:18:44,260
No. She will think it that way.

394
00:18:44,500 --> 00:18:45,380
I came to see you today

395
00:18:45,380 --> 00:18:47,540
to beg you to put in a good word
for Mei Yushan and me.

396
00:18:47,540 --> 00:18:48,420
I'll be fine either way.

397
00:18:48,420 --> 00:18:50,180
But she's a lady with a delicate body.

398
00:18:50,180 --> 00:18:51,180
Nothing can happen to her.

399
00:19:20,790 --> 00:19:25,490
[Nangong Yao]

400
00:20:07,780 --> 00:20:08,620
Douzi,

401
00:20:08,980 --> 00:20:09,940
don't go.

402
00:20:31,500 --> 00:20:32,220
Not bad.

403
00:20:32,780 --> 00:20:33,860
Great progress.

404
00:20:34,060 --> 00:20:35,140
Of course.

405
00:20:35,900 --> 00:20:37,140
I'm sixteen now.

406
00:20:37,260 --> 00:20:38,100
I'm no longer

407
00:20:38,100 --> 00:20:39,980
the little girl
who couldn't protect herself.

408
00:20:41,700 --> 00:20:42,580
Yeah.

409
00:20:42,980 --> 00:20:45,540
You're no longer the little girl
who escaped from Shengdong

410
00:20:46,380 --> 00:20:47,740
and came to me

411
00:20:47,780 --> 00:20:49,780
in tears begging for something to eat.

412
00:20:50,420 --> 00:20:52,060
You're all grown up now.

413
00:20:52,900 --> 00:20:54,540
It's time to find you a husband.

414
00:20:55,820 --> 00:20:57,140
I don't need a husband.

415
00:20:57,860 --> 00:20:58,740
What about you, Sir?

416
00:20:58,740 --> 00:21:00,020
Do you plan to stay unmarried forever?

417
00:21:01,780 --> 00:21:02,940
I have my plans.

418
00:21:03,460 --> 00:21:04,460
Don't ask too much

419
00:21:05,020 --> 00:21:05,740
about my business.

420
00:21:06,020 --> 00:21:06,980
Then don't ask too much

421
00:21:06,980 --> 00:21:07,900
about my business.

422
00:21:31,180 --> 00:21:32,700
You really can't see

423
00:21:32,940 --> 00:21:34,380
how I feel about you?

424
00:21:41,940 --> 00:21:43,060
Sorry to disturb you this late.

425
00:21:43,100 --> 00:21:44,620
The madam heard
that our lady fell into the water.

426
00:21:44,620 --> 00:21:45,940
So she couldn't wait to visit her.

427
00:21:46,580 --> 00:21:47,500
I understand.

428
00:21:49,780 --> 00:21:50,660
Normally,

429
00:21:51,060 --> 00:21:52,740
we don't allow visitors at this time.

430
00:21:52,820 --> 00:21:55,020
Please don't take too long, madam.

431
00:21:55,460 --> 00:21:57,060
I can't go in there.

432
00:21:57,460 --> 00:21:59,460
You two can just walk along this road.

433
00:21:59,860 --> 00:22:00,820
Thank you.

434
00:22:18,060 --> 00:22:19,620
Madam, after we cross the bridge,

435
00:22:19,620 --> 00:22:21,140
the most beautiful room will be the one.

436
00:22:23,380 --> 00:22:24,220
Shan,

437
00:22:24,380 --> 00:22:25,460
I'm here to see you.

438
00:22:26,100 --> 00:22:27,100
Put the stuff here.

439
00:22:30,260 --> 00:22:31,140
You wait outside.

440
00:22:31,540 --> 00:22:32,660
Yes, madam.

441
00:22:42,220 --> 00:22:43,020
Shan.

442
00:22:43,340 --> 00:22:44,100
Shan?

443
00:22:46,420 --> 00:22:47,500
I don't understand you.

444
00:22:47,500 --> 00:22:49,220
You refused to take Cui with you,

445
00:22:49,460 --> 00:22:51,940
insisting on coming here alone
to suffer.

446
00:22:52,020 --> 00:22:53,460
You almost lost your life.

447
00:22:53,740 --> 00:22:55,540
You're breaking my heart, you know?

448
00:22:58,780 --> 00:22:59,620
Shan?

449
00:23:04,140 --> 00:23:05,740
Why is it so hot?

450
00:23:06,180 --> 00:23:07,700
Did you catch a cold?

451
00:23:08,620 --> 00:23:09,500
Shan.

452
00:23:09,980 --> 00:23:11,340
Good girl, let me take a look.

453
00:23:12,300 --> 00:23:13,020
Mother.

454
00:23:13,020 --> 00:23:13,900
Who are you?

455
00:23:14,060 --> 00:23:16,300
What... What are you doing
in my daughter's room?

456
00:23:22,900 --> 00:23:23,700
Stay here.

457
00:23:23,740 --> 00:23:24,540
Don't make a sound.

458
00:23:27,980 --> 00:23:28,900
Yao.

459
00:23:30,660 --> 00:23:31,260
Mother.

460
00:23:33,020 --> 00:23:34,140
Why are you in such a hurry?

461
00:23:34,380 --> 00:23:35,340
What are you here for?

462
00:23:36,700 --> 00:23:38,220
I heard you fell into the water.

463
00:23:38,380 --> 00:23:39,900
Of course, I'm in a hurry to see you.

464
00:23:40,540 --> 00:23:41,980
Why didn't you call the physicians?

465
00:23:42,300 --> 00:23:43,180
I am fine.

466
00:23:45,700 --> 00:23:47,500
You're afraid I'll punish someone,
aren't you?

467
00:23:48,540 --> 00:23:49,500
That girl.

468
00:23:49,660 --> 00:23:51,980
She is a lady but she acts rashly.

469
00:23:52,540 --> 00:23:53,540
If I don't discipline her,

470
00:23:53,540 --> 00:23:55,420
there will be chaos in the palace.

471
00:23:55,420 --> 00:23:56,060
Mother.

472
00:24:00,180 --> 00:24:00,900
Who's in there?

473
00:24:00,900 --> 00:24:01,700
Mother, stop.

474
00:24:02,460 --> 00:24:03,220
Why?

475
00:24:03,580 --> 00:24:05,180
You were just talking about manners.

476
00:24:05,340 --> 00:24:05,940
Look, I'm...

477
00:24:05,940 --> 00:24:07,460
You've finished taking a shower.

478
00:24:07,780 --> 00:24:08,980
Why can't I go in now?

479
00:24:09,140 --> 00:24:09,780
Step aside.

480
00:24:14,420 --> 00:24:15,020
Mother.

481
00:24:31,940 --> 00:24:33,300
When you were showering,

482
00:24:33,620 --> 00:24:35,620
didn't Nanbei
stay at your service in here?

483
00:24:35,940 --> 00:24:37,460
You are the Crown Prince.

484
00:24:37,460 --> 00:24:39,580
Do you have to do everything yourself?

485
00:24:41,060 --> 00:24:42,820
It would be inconvenient

486
00:24:43,420 --> 00:24:45,260
if they were here
when I was taking a shower.

487
00:24:54,300 --> 00:24:56,740
You haven't changed the furnishings
in the study for two years, right?

488
00:24:56,740 --> 00:24:59,220
Why don't you
get the servants to change them?

489
00:24:59,500 --> 00:25:00,100
Mother.

490
00:25:02,300 --> 00:25:04,180
I'm used to them.

491
00:25:04,380 --> 00:25:05,180
If I had them changed,

492
00:25:05,420 --> 00:25:06,260
I'd feel uncomfortable.

493
00:25:07,420 --> 00:25:09,540
Thrift is a good thing.

494
00:25:09,540 --> 00:25:10,700
If your father knows,

495
00:25:10,700 --> 00:25:12,420
he will be very happy.

496
00:25:12,980 --> 00:25:14,460
But you are the Crown Prince,

497
00:25:14,460 --> 00:25:16,060
you must have what you deserve.

498
00:25:16,060 --> 00:25:16,660
Mother!

499
00:25:27,860 --> 00:25:28,460
Mother,

500
00:25:29,340 --> 00:25:30,660
I just received some new tea.

501
00:25:30,900 --> 00:25:31,900
Let me brew it for you.

502
00:25:32,740 --> 00:25:34,660
You've never invited me to tea.

503
00:25:34,660 --> 00:25:36,260
Why are you in the mood today?

504
00:25:36,260 --> 00:25:37,700
Mother, this tea is very different.

505
00:25:40,740 --> 00:25:41,340
Mother,

506
00:25:41,700 --> 00:25:42,500
this tea is different

507
00:25:43,500 --> 00:25:44,540
from anything you had before.

508
00:25:44,940 --> 00:25:46,260
I don't want tea.

509
00:25:46,260 --> 00:25:48,500
Mother, this tea is very different.

510
00:25:50,420 --> 00:25:51,260
Really different.

511
00:25:54,420 --> 00:25:55,140
Trust me.

512
00:25:55,580 --> 00:25:56,420
This tea...

513
00:26:03,100 --> 00:26:03,740
Mother,

514
00:26:04,380 --> 00:26:06,340
this tea's flavor turns from bitterness
to sweetness after drinking it.

515
00:26:07,140 --> 00:26:08,140
Come on, Mother.

516
00:26:08,540 --> 00:26:09,500
Sit here.

517
00:26:09,660 --> 00:26:10,260
Come on.

518
00:26:11,220 --> 00:26:11,820
Here.

519
00:26:15,460 --> 00:26:16,380
Zuo, You.

520
00:26:16,780 --> 00:26:19,340
Get my tea ready for me.

521
00:26:19,460 --> 00:26:20,380
You know which one it is.

522
00:26:27,220 --> 00:26:27,860
Mother,

523
00:26:28,860 --> 00:26:30,260
you aren't suspecting me hiding beauties

524
00:26:30,580 --> 00:26:31,900
in the Eastern Palace, are you?

525
00:26:35,100 --> 00:26:35,980
Mother, don't worry.

526
00:26:36,340 --> 00:26:37,740
If I am interested in someone,

527
00:26:37,980 --> 00:26:39,260
though she stays
in the Eastern Palace...

528
00:26:42,860 --> 00:26:44,460
If it's Mei Yushan,

529
00:26:45,300 --> 00:26:46,900
my answer is no.

530
00:26:50,460 --> 00:26:51,940
If it's someone I don't like,

531
00:26:52,060 --> 00:26:52,860
my answer is also no.

532
00:26:59,180 --> 00:27:00,780
Rich people are just different.

533
00:27:00,900 --> 00:27:02,860
Even the chamber pot is made of jade.

534
00:27:07,900 --> 00:27:08,900
Mother.

535
00:27:13,260 --> 00:27:14,300
Step aside.

536
00:27:18,460 --> 00:27:20,620
That Mei Yushan of the Mei Family

537
00:27:20,620 --> 00:27:22,340
used to be intelligent and elegant.

538
00:27:22,660 --> 00:27:24,420
I quite liked her then.

539
00:27:24,660 --> 00:27:25,900
But after she came to the palace,

540
00:27:25,900 --> 00:27:27,460
she somehow changed
into a different person.

541
00:27:31,860 --> 00:27:32,660
What?

542
00:27:38,580 --> 00:27:40,420
No manners at all.

543
00:27:41,020 --> 00:27:42,260
Yet, you just have

544
00:27:42,820 --> 00:27:44,140
to defend her.

545
00:27:48,220 --> 00:27:49,100
Step aside.

546
00:28:00,860 --> 00:28:01,500
You.

547
00:28:02,460 --> 00:28:03,540
Get dressed.

548
00:28:04,140 --> 00:28:04,900
It's cold.

549
00:28:05,780 --> 00:28:06,580
Yes, Mother.

550
00:28:14,140 --> 00:28:14,780
Douzi?

551
00:28:20,880 --> 00:28:25,460
[Eastern Palace]

552
00:28:25,460 --> 00:28:26,100
Your Majesty,

553
00:28:26,580 --> 00:28:27,860
as you ordered,

554
00:28:27,860 --> 00:28:29,820
peony water is ready
for you to bathe in.

555
00:28:29,820 --> 00:28:31,540
The peony is blooming beautifully today.

556
00:28:31,540 --> 00:28:33,620
I asked servants to pick
more than two hundred flowers to...

557
00:28:33,620 --> 00:28:34,660
We aren't going to the Huacai Hall.

558
00:28:35,620 --> 00:28:36,780
Let's go to the Guixiu Pavilion.

559
00:28:37,100 --> 00:28:37,860
